	<center>
		<h1>Cleartext sensitive information transmission</h1>
		<hr>
	</center>
	<ul>
            <li>Passwords are sent in cleartext over the wire</li>
            <li>Malicious users can sniff passwords and use them to impersonate legitimate users</li>
            <li>Possible remedies</li>
            <ul>
                <li>Digest-MD5: use special one-use tokens to ensure the user knows password, without revealing password
                <li>Any number of public key solutions</li>
            </ul>
	</ul>
